# LapyTrack — Deployment

## Production URLs
| Service | URL |
|---------|-----|
| Frontend | https://lapy-track.vercel.app |
| Backend API | https://lapytrack.onrender.com |
| Health check | https://lapytrack.onrender.com/api/ |
| GitHub | https://github.com/kforkreativein/lapytrack |

## Auto-deploy flow
Push to `main` → Render rebuilds backend (Docker, root `Dockerfile`) → Vercel rebuilds frontend (project `frontend`, root dir `frontend/`)

## Backend env (Render dashboard)
```
MONGO_URL=mongodb+srv://...
DB_NAME=krish_computer_db
JWT_SECRET=<strong-random-string>
FRONTEND_URL=https://lapy-track.vercel.app
CORS_ORIGINS=https://lapy-track.vercel.app
```

## Frontend env (Vercel → project `frontend` → Production)
```
REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL=https://lapytrack.onrender.com
```

## MongoDB Atlas
- Network Access must allow `0.0.0.0/0` (Render has dynamic IPs)
- Menu: **SECURITY → Database & Network Access → IP Access List**

## Render free tier
- Sleeps after ~15 min idle → first request can take 30–60s
- Use UptimeRobot pinging `/api/` every 5 min to keep warm (optional)
- After MongoDB whitelist changes, **Manual Deploy** on Render if backend still down

## Local dev
```bash
# Backend (port 8000)
cd backend && source .venv/bin/activate && uvicorn server:app --reload --port 8000

# Frontend (port 3000)
cd frontend && yarn start
# .env.local: REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:8000
```

## Troubleshooting checklist
1. Backend 502/timeout → Render logs, MongoDB IP whitelist, `MONGO_URL`
2. Frontend can't reach API → `REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL` on Vercel, redeploy frontend
3. Login/cookies fail → `CORS_ORIGINS` + `FRONTEND_URL` on Render; cookies use `secure=True` when HTTPS
4. Job sheet photos 404 → file may be gone after Render redeploy (ephemeral uploads)
